content: Unresponsive developers. VERY useful app though.
When i first got the app the time (delay) processing my score was just seconds. Now it is over 10 second which seems like an eternity

Continues to crash which is counter productive to my therapy and is expensive at $9.99, not only that when you ask for either help or your money back they give you the run around and don't return your email requesting updates. Extremely unprofessional!
I have never complained about an app before. This app barely works. It errs out after most of the features. Save your money.
unable to play any of the programmes, very annoying!!! :-(
When I go to send my results the application keeps crashing, have uninstalled it and re installed it but it still keeps happening
Can't open the app at all.
The 12/21/18 update has crashed this app making it unusable.
This app was recommended by physical therapist as part of my treatment plan.  Doing exactly what I expected and the various levels in each area help with improving brain to foot reconnections.

A great app when used in conjunction with the GMI program, but it is missing a few key features. The ability to see cards that you got wrong, this would be good for recognizing patterns of wrong answers.
The results cant be accessed after 1 month and are sent as back results.

Would like more information on how to use this app, how often you should use it, if it is better to use when pain at its worst or at its best, when to advance through the program. Also on Android phone some of the input screens are partially chopped off rotating device doesn't help

Such a better user interface then the previous app. Being able to see scores in graph form also helps to track progress and trends. Having the added benefit of being able to send the information directly to my clinician is great.
